-Sorry about that.

263
00:09:55,081 --> 00:09:55,881
-Oh, it's all right.

264
00:09:55,914 --> 00:09:57,547
Don't worry.

265
00:09:57,581 --> 00:09:58,981
-What do you want to do?

266
00:09:59,014 --> 00:10:01,281
-Well if you think this man
Kisuke can do something,

267
00:10:01,314 --> 00:10:03,347
then I guess I'll wait
till he comes back.

268
00:10:03,381 --> 00:10:05,647
There's really nothing
else we can do.

269
00:10:05,681 --> 00:10:07,047
-Mm hm.

270
00:10:07,081 --> 00:10:08,481
[cat meows]

271
00:10:08,514 --> 00:10:10,447
-Thank you, Ururu.

272
00:10:10,481 --> 00:10:13,447
-Hm?

273
00:10:13,481 --> 00:10:14,947
[gasp] Hollows!

274
00:10:14,981 --> 00:10:18,947
They've come here now.

275
00:10:18,981 --> 00:10:20,447
Hurry, inside!

276
00:10:20,481 --> 00:10:22,447
[howling]

277
00:10:22,481 --> 00:10:24,447
-Go out the back door!

278
00:10:24,481 --> 00:10:27,414
-Ururu!

279
00:10:27,447 --> 00:10:29,414
[cat meows]
Everything's all right.

280
00:10:29,447 --> 00:10:30,181
Don't worry.

281
00:10:30,214 --> 00:10:30,847
I'll protect you.

282
00:10:38,014 --> 00:10:39,181
-Damnit!

283
00:10:39,214 --> 00:10:41,481
How long is he going to
keep us waiting like this?

284
00:10:41,514 --> 00:10:43,714
DON KANONJI (OFFSCREEN):
Sorry to keep you waiting.

285
00:10:43,747 --> 00:10:46,514
Boys and girls!

286
00:10:46,547 --> 00:10:52,181
[coughing] The century's
premiere spiritualist,

287
00:10:52,214 --> 00:10:54,414
Don Kanonji, at your service!

288
00:10:54,447 --> 00:10:56,247
-You wanted to
see my true power?

289
00:10:56,281 --> 00:10:58,547
Then ready or not, here I go!

290
00:10:58,581 --> 00:10:59,447
-I'm coming too!

291
00:10:59,481 --> 00:11:01,381
-Hold your horses!

292
00:11:01,414 --> 00:11:03,681
[yelling] Now just
wait a minute, kids.

293
00:11:03,714 --> 00:11:06,181
You don't think that
I'm the enemy, do you?

294
00:11:06,214 --> 00:11:07,114
-Huh?

295
00:11:07,147 --> 00:11:08,414
-Come on now kids,
think about it.

296
00:11:08,447 --> 00:11:11,081
What's the point in heroes
trying to fight each other?

297
00:11:11,114 --> 00:11:11,881
-Well.

298
00:11:11,914 --> 00:11:12,947
-There is none.

299
00:11:12,981 --> 00:11:14,947
But seriously, I've
been kicking around

300
00:11:14,981 --> 00:11:17,214
the idea of creating
a special team of kids

301
00:11:17,247 --> 00:11:20,047
just like you-- kind-hearted,
self-sacrificing kids

302
00:11:20,081 --> 00:11:22,181
with their own special
powers who share my vision

303
00:11:22,214 --> 00:11:24,847
and want to join me in keeping
the peace in this town!

304
00:11:24,881 --> 00:11:26,181
-Huh?

305
00:11:26,214 --> 00:11:28,781
-And this team would be called
the Karakura Superheroes!

306
00:11:28,814 --> 00:11:31,181
You know the entertainment
world is youth-oriented.

307
00:11:31,214 --> 00:11:33,781
Everyone's looking for any grade
schooler with special talents

308
00:11:33,814 --> 00:11:35,181
to become the next big thing.

309
00:11:35,214 --> 00:11:37,781
Well if you ask me, you
two have the potential

310
00:11:37,814 --> 00:11:39,047
to shoot right to the top.

311
00:11:39,081 --> 00:11:39,947
Well how about it?

312
00:11:39,981 --> 00:11:40,881
Will you form a unit--

313
00:11:40,914 --> 00:11:42,081
-(IN HEAD) So long winded.

314
00:11:42,114 --> 00:11:43,714
-(IN HEAD) This is stupid.

315
00:11:43,747 --> 00:11:45,981
-And I'm happy to inform
you that since both of you

316
00:11:46,014 --> 00:11:48,681
are the first two Karakura
Superheroes I've recruited,

317
00:11:48,714 --> 00:11:49,347
guess what!

318
00:11:49,381 --> 00:11:50,247
It's your lucky day!

319
00:11:50,281 --> 00:11:51,647
The red position is still open!

320
00:11:51,681 --> 00:11:52,881
-Uh, red?

321
00:11:52,914 --> 00:11:53,847
-It's the lead.

322
00:11:53,881 --> 00:11:55,081
Oh and did I mention
that I intend

323
00:11:55,114 --> 00:11:56,847
to turn this little
project into a segment

324
00:11:56,881 --> 00:11:59,081
on my top-rated
Spirit Hunter TV show?

325
00:11:59,114 --> 00:11:59,814
-Television!

326
00:11:59,847 --> 00:12:01,014
-I'm in!

327
00:12:01,047 --> 00:12:03,014
-Well, then I guess I'll
have no choice, since it's

328
00:12:03,047 --> 00:12:05,581
an opportunity to keep the
peace in Karakura town.

329
00:12:05,614 --> 00:12:06,847
-OK!

330
00:12:06,881 --> 00:12:10,214
Your enthusiasm has gotten
you a place on the squad!

331
00:12:10,247 --> 00:12:13,414
-Great since no one
objects, I'll be red, OK?

332
00:12:13,447 --> 00:12:14,247
-Hey!

333
00:12:14,281 --> 00:12:15,314
You can't just decide like that!

334
00:12:15,347 --> 00:12:15,881
I'm red!

335
00:12:15,914 --> 00:12:16,347
You got that?

336
00:12:16,381 --> 00:12:17,214
Me, red!

337
00:12:17,247 --> 00:12:17,881
Red, me!

338
00:12:17,914 --> 00:12:19,014
-Shut your pie hole.

339
00:12:19,047 --> 00:12:20,681
Come on, you know
better than that.

340
00:12:20,714 --> 00:12:21,814
No girl can be red.

341
00:12:21,847 --> 00:12:22,581
-What?

342
00:12:22,614 --> 00:12:23,947
Are you looking for a fight?

343
00:12:23,981 --> 00:12:25,981
-Oh man, what a
pain in the butt.

344
00:12:26,014 --> 00:12:27,247
-Ugh!

345
00:12:27,281 --> 00:12:29,647
There is absolutely no way
I'm going to let you be red!

346
00:12:29,681 --> 00:12:31,047
-That's it.

347
00:12:31,081 --> 00:12:32,381
Get ready for our first job.

348
00:12:32,414 --> 00:12:34,281
She's in terrible danger.

349
00:12:34,314 --> 00:12:36,381
Bad spirits are
after your sister.

350
00:12:36,414 --> 00:12:38,614
-I can't understand a
single word he's saying.

351
00:12:38,647 --> 00:12:52,514
[panting] [gasp]

352
00:13:00,981 --> 00:13:02,414
[gasp]

353
00:13:04,209 --> 00:13:05,251
-Cammy?

354
00:13:05,251 --> 00:13:07,090
[hiss]

355
00:13:15,947 --> 00:13:16,413
-Cammy?

356
00:13:21,913 --> 00:13:23,913
[roar]

357
00:13:23,947 --> 00:13:25,380
[yells]

358
00:13:25,413 --> 00:13:26,947
-Smells like bad spirits!

359
00:13:30,813 --> 00:13:32,680
Huh?

360
00:13:32,713 --> 00:13:33,780
-Not this time!

361
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:34,780
[bang]

362
00:13:34,813 --> 00:13:37,247
[screaming]

363
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:38,247
-Cammy?

364
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:40,713
[cat meows]

365
00:13:40,747 --> 00:13:42,180
-Oh Cammy.

366
00:13:42,213 --> 00:13:43,647
Huh?

367
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:46,680
-Sorry to have kept you waiting
little girl but there's no need

368
00:13:46,713 --> 00:13:49,180
to worry anymore
because we're here!

369
00:13:49,213 --> 00:13:52,847
-Karakura Red-- Karin Kurosaki!

370
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:57,613
-And the real Karakura
Red-- Jinta Hanakari!

371
00:13:57,647 --> 00:13:59,980
-Hey, just one minute
there jerk face.

372
00:14:00,013 --> 00:14:01,280
What do you think you're doing?

373
00:14:01,313 --> 00:14:02,047
Didn't you hear me?

374
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:02,780
I'm red, got it?

375
00:14:02,813 --> 00:14:03,780
-Would you shut up?

376
00:14:03,813 --> 00:14:04,780
It's already decided!

377
00:14:04,813 --> 00:14:05,580
I'm red!

378
00:14:05,613 --> 00:14:07,280
-No way I'm definitely red!

379
00:14:07,313 --> 00:14:08,313
Red is me!

380
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:09,613
-Look, this is what
we're going to do.

381
00:14:09,647 --> 00:14:11,780
We'll decide who will be red
based on your performance

382
00:14:11,813 --> 00:14:13,080
today, OK?

383
00:14:13,113 --> 00:14:13,580
-Huh?

384
00:14:13,613 --> 00:14:14,347
-Yeah!

385
00:14:14,380 --> 00:14:15,480
-I'll show you who's red!

386
00:14:15,513 --> 00:14:16,480
-Don Kanonji!

387
00:14:16,513 --> 00:14:17,980
And Karin, too!

388
00:14:18,013 --> 00:14:19,947
[howling]

389
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:23,813
-Secret attack!

390
00:14:23,847 --> 00:14:25,480
Super spirit javelin!

391
00:14:25,513 --> 00:14:27,513
With this device you can
reach any bad spirit.

392
00:14:27,547 --> 00:14:28,947
With detachable
saw and solid grip,

393
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:30,513
even high branches are a breeze.

394
00:14:30,547 --> 00:14:33,713
These extendable pruning sheers
are so easy to manouv-- oh!

395
00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:35,147
How dare you!

396
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:36,880
Come back and fight
me you coward!

397
00:14:36,913 --> 00:14:38,247
-You're too slow!

398
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:39,180
Beat it!

399
00:14:39,213 --> 00:14:40,113
Go on, scram!

400
00:14:40,147 --> 00:14:40,947
-Oh yeah, come on!

401
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:42,480
You show 'em, sister!

402
00:14:42,513 --> 00:14:45,613
I shall entreat the super
spirit of the javelin to you!

403
00:14:45,647 --> 00:14:46,247
[laughing]

404
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:47,980
-The lead is mine!

405
00:14:48,013 --> 00:14:52,813
-And now batting cleanup,
number 55, Jinta Hanakari!

406
00:14:52,847 --> 00:14:53,647
-Aha!

407
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:55,013
Excellent swing!

408
00:14:55,047 --> 00:14:57,380
Who could ever forget
an effort like that?

409
00:14:57,413 --> 00:14:58,780
You're the super star of suave!

410
00:14:58,813 --> 00:14:59,747
-That's right!

411
00:14:59,780 --> 00:15:01,713
It's only natural
because I'm red!

412
00:15:01,747 --> 00:15:02,713
-Karin!

413
00:15:02,747 --> 00:15:04,680
-Hey Yuzu, get away!

414
00:15:04,713 --> 00:15:06,113
-OK.

415
00:15:06,147 --> 00:15:06,613
-Oh?

416
00:15:06,647 --> 00:15:07,247
Huh?

417
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,080
-Hey wait hold it!

418
00:15:09,113 --> 00:15:11,013
I'm right behind you Yuzu!

419
00:15:11,047 --> 00:15:11,513
-Huh?

420
00:15:11,547 --> 00:15:12,513
-Stay down!

421
00:15:16,447 --> 00:15:18,847
-Ururu?

422
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:19,413
-Huh?

423
00:15:19,447 --> 00:15:20,313
What is this?

424
00:15:20,347 --> 00:15:22,313
Another one of the
new generation?

425
00:15:22,347 --> 00:15:23,347
Wonderful!

426
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:25,480
There are so many
red candidates here!

427
00:15:25,513 --> 00:15:28,247
-Aw, Ururu, showing up
out of the blue like that.

428
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:30,480
Well listen, you're not
taking the red title from me!

429
00:15:30,513 --> 00:15:34,013
-How many times do I have
to tell you, you're not red!

430
00:15:34,047 --> 00:15:36,580
-OK, rule number
one-- only the recruit

431
00:15:36,613 --> 00:15:38,047
who gives a number
one performance

432
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:40,380
deserves the title of red!

433
00:15:40,413 --> 00:15:42,280
-I am not going to lose!

434
00:15:42,313 --> 00:15:42,847
-Oh yeah?

435
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,180
I'll show you!

436
00:15:44,213 --> 00:15:46,547
[yelling]

437
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:47,747
-This is great!

438
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:50,513
The Karakura superheroes
are born right here today!

439
00:15:50,547 --> 00:15:51,613
[laughing]

440
00:15:51,647 --> 00:15:55,213
-Aren't you going to
fight too, Don Kanonji?

441
00:15:55,247 --> 00:15:56,480
-Hey kids!

442
00:15:56,513 --> 00:15:58,813
That kind of fighting won't
earn you the title of red!

443
00:15:58,847 --> 00:16:00,180
-(GROANING) Useless!

444
00:16:00,213 --> 00:16:03,413
Hey, maybe I can use that
soccer ball over there!

445
00:16:03,447 --> 00:16:05,980
[grunts] Score!

446
00:16:06,013 --> 00:16:08,147
So, do you see the power of red?

447
00:16:08,180 --> 00:16:09,547
-Like I said, I'm
red, understand?

448
00:16:20,247 --> 00:16:22,647
[gasping]

449
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:25,080
[howling]

450
00:16:25,113 --> 00:16:26,380
-What's that?

451
00:16:26,413 --> 00:16:28,780
-So you're finally making an
appearance, eh, bad spirit

452
00:16:28,813 --> 00:16:29,280
king?

453
00:16:29,313 --> 00:16:31,013
[stomping]

454
00:16:31,047 --> 00:16:32,347
-It's coming this way!

455
00:16:32,380 --> 00:16:33,680
-What do you say there children?

456
00:16:33,713 --> 00:16:36,647
This looks like a job for
the Karakura Superheroes!

457
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:37,880
-Yeah!

458
00:16:37,913 --> 00:16:39,480
-But before we attack,
let's go over our strategy.

459
00:16:39,513 --> 00:16:40,613
-Are you nuts?

460
00:16:40,647 --> 00:16:42,580
We don't have time!

461
00:16:42,613 --> 00:16:43,580
[howling]

462
00:16:43,613 --> 00:16:44,580
[yelling]

463
00:16:44,613 --> 00:16:51,547
[crash]

464
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:52,513
[screams]

465
00:16:52,547 --> 00:16:53,013
-Yuzu!

466
00:16:59,480 --> 00:16:59,947
-Cammy.

467
00:17:03,447 --> 00:17:06,913
[roar]

468
00:17:06,947 --> 00:17:07,413
[gasps]

469
00:17:07,447 --> 00:17:07,913
-Yuzu!

470
00:17:10,913 --> 00:17:11,580
No!

471
00:17:11,613 --> 00:17:13,180
-What's that down there?

472
00:17:13,213 --> 00:17:15,147
URURU (OFFSCREEN): Do
you think it's an ally?

473
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:16,813
DON KANONJI (OFFSCREEN):
It's a miracle!

474
00:17:16,847 --> 00:17:20,613
Our combined desire for
just called forth a miracle!

475
00:17:20,647 --> 00:17:22,580
[crash]

476
00:17:22,613 --> 00:17:24,113
[screams]

477
00:17:24,147 --> 00:17:25,813
DON KANONJI (OFFSCREEN):
That is the hero

478
00:17:25,847 --> 00:17:27,213
robot sent to us by the gods.

479
00:17:27,247 --> 00:17:29,547
Karakura's sonic lion!

480
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:39,780
[screams]

481
00:17:39,813 --> 00:17:42,913
-It's time for us to
join the sonic lion too!

482
00:17:42,947 --> 00:17:43,847
Let's go!

483
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:48,347
[yelling]

484
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:49,113
-Hold together!

485
00:17:49,147 --> 00:17:50,547
Karakura attack formation!

486
00:17:53,913 --> 00:17:55,180
Karakura canon!

487
00:17:55,213 --> 00:17:58,180
Karakura gold [gong] Yeah!

488
00:17:58,213 --> 00:18:01,980
Feel the wrath of the golden
cannonballs of justice!

489
00:18:02,013 --> 00:18:03,947
Wah!

490
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:05,447
-Ah!

491
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:07,413
Jinta home run!

492
00:18:07,447 --> 00:18:08,880
-Karin style!

493
00:18:08,913 --> 00:18:09,880
Dance shot!

494
00:18:09,913 --> 00:18:11,347
[crash]

495
00:18:11,380 --> 00:18:12,813
-It's coming, Ururu!

496
00:18:12,847 --> 00:18:13,313
-OK!

497
00:18:16,780 --> 00:18:19,580
[roar]

498
00:18:19,613 --> 00:18:21,980
-The Karakura
Superheroes prevail!

499
00:18:22,013 --> 00:18:23,347
And our mission
was accomplished!

500
00:18:23,380 --> 00:18:26,347
Wa ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!

501
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:28,480
KARIN (OFFSCREEN): Did
that thing really work?

502
00:18:28,513 --> 00:18:30,380
DON KANONJI (OFFSCREEN):
Why of course it did!

503
00:18:30,413 --> 00:18:32,613
It delivered the final blow!

504
00:18:32,647 --> 00:18:34,980
JINTA (OFFSCREEN): No way.

505
00:18:35,013 --> 00:18:37,313
YUZU (OFFSCREEN):
Oh, I remember now.

506
00:18:37,347 --> 00:18:39,480
I did meet Cammy before.

507
00:18:39,513 --> 00:18:40,180
It was raining.

508
00:18:40,213 --> 00:18:41,647
[gasp]

509
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:43,113
[cat meows]

510
00:18:43,147 --> 00:18:44,580
[gasp]

511
00:18:44,613 --> 00:18:47,980
-Oh, here, here you go.

512
00:18:55,780 --> 00:18:56,713
See you later.

513
00:19:01,580 --> 00:19:02,847
Oh.

514
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:05,413
[cat meows]

515
00:19:05,447 --> 00:19:07,313
[tires screeching]

516
00:19:07,347 --> 00:19:08,347
[gasp]

517
00:19:08,380 --> 00:19:09,613
YUZU (OFFSCREEN):
If I hadn't come by,

518
00:19:09,647 --> 00:19:12,013
then Cammy wouldn't
have had to die.

519
00:19:12,047 --> 00:19:15,813
I thought maybe you'd
hold a grudge against me.

520
00:19:15,847 --> 00:19:16,313
But--

521
00:19:20,247 --> 00:19:22,180
[cat meows]

522
00:19:22,213 --> 00:19:24,413
-Cammy.

523
00:19:24,447 --> 00:19:25,413
-Yuzu.

524
00:19:25,447 --> 00:19:26,813
[gasp]

525
00:19:26,847 --> 00:19:27,313
-Karin!

526
00:19:30,180 --> 00:19:32,380
-Thank goodness!

527
00:19:32,413 --> 00:19:33,113
-Huh?

528
00:19:33,147 --> 00:19:34,713
What happened?

529
00:19:34,747 --> 00:19:37,213
-You see, the legendary
Karakura sonic lion,

530
00:19:37,247 --> 00:19:39,580
which was properly summoned
through our extreme power

531
00:19:39,613 --> 00:19:43,680
of justice, was responsible
for saving your life.

532
00:19:43,713 --> 00:19:45,013
-He's right!

533
00:19:45,047 --> 00:19:48,180
Together we all summoned this
absolutely amazing thing!

534
00:19:48,213 --> 00:19:49,947
-Hey, I don't see him anywhere.

535
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:50,780
Where'd he go.

536
00:19:50,813 --> 00:19:51,313
KARIN (OFFSCREEN): That's right.

537
00:19:51,347 --> 00:19:52,147
[cat meows]

538
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:53,447
KARIN (OFFSCREEN): He's gone.

539
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:54,947
JINTA (OFFSCREEN): Too bad,
you should have seen him.

540
00:19:54,980 --> 00:19:56,347
[laughing]

541
00:19:56,380 --> 00:19:57,647
-Secret?

542
00:19:57,680 --> 00:20:00,047
[cat meows]

543
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:01,480
-All right then.

544
00:20:01,513 --> 00:20:03,847
I guess that it can
be our little secret.

545
00:20:06,613 --> 00:20:07,213
-What!

546
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:09,580
-What's happening?

547
00:20:09,613 --> 00:20:12,480
[gasps]

548
00:20:12,513 --> 00:20:13,913
-It's for the best.

549
00:20:13,947 --> 00:20:15,047
I'm glad though.

550
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:17,180
I think that it was
able to pass on.

551
00:20:17,213 --> 00:20:20,947
-Um, so then does that mean that
the cat was really a spirit?

552
00:20:20,980 --> 00:20:23,280
-If that's what happened
then it was probably

553
00:20:23,313 --> 00:20:26,213
able to come to terms with
whatever regrets it had.

554
00:20:26,247 --> 00:20:27,447
[crying]

555
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:27,947
-Huh?

556
00:20:27,980 --> 00:20:29,047
[crying]

557
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:33,347
-I wasn't able to do
anything for Cammy.

558
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:34,313
Nothing!

559
00:20:34,347 --> 00:20:36,713
I couldn't do
anything for Cammy!

560
00:20:36,747 --> 00:20:39,580
[crying]

561
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:43,880
-Hey, uh-- see that was just
his way of saying thanks to you

562
00:20:43,913 --> 00:20:45,080
just now.

563
00:20:45,113 --> 00:20:45,880
-Is that true?

564
00:20:45,913 --> 00:20:47,047
-Of course it is!

565
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:49,347
A man senses these things, OK?

566
00:20:49,380 --> 00:20:50,813
-I hope it's true!

567
00:20:50,847 --> 00:20:52,313
I hope it's true!

568
00:20:52,347 --> 00:20:56,813
[crying]

569
00:20:56,847 --> 00:20:59,280
-There, there.

570
00:20:59,313 --> 00:21:01,613
-(IN HEAD) Cammy, thank you.

571
00:21:05,488 --> 00:21:09,754
-Karakura pink--
Ururu Tsumugiya.

572
00:21:09,788 --> 00:21:13,688
-Karakura red-- Karin Kurosaki.

